        "parts": [
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": "892 - "
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": "وَقَالَ أَبُو جَعْفَرٍ لِمُحَمَّدِ بْنِ مُسْلِمٍ: «يَا مُحَمَّدَ بْنَ مُسْلِمٍ لاَ تَدَعَنَّ ذِكْرَ اَللَّهِ عَلَى كُلِّ حَالٍ"
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": " وَ "
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": "لَوْ سَمِعْتَ اَلْمُنَادِيَ يُنَادِي بِالْأَذَانِ"
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": " وَ "
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": "أَنْتَ عَلَى اَلْخَلاَءِ فَاذْكُرِ اَللَّهَ عَزَّ"
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": " وَ "
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": "جَلَّ"
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": " وَ "
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": "قُلْ كَمَا"
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": " يَقُولُ"
          }
        ]
      },
      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:1:45:28",
      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/45/892",
      "text": [
        " اَلْمُؤَذِّنُ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.892 - Imam Muhammad ibn Ali Al-Baqir (as) said to Muhammad ibn Muslim:\n\"O’ Muhammad ibn Muslim, never neglect the remembrance of Allah (swt) in any situation. Even if you hear the caller calling the adhan while you are in a state of relieving yourself, remember Allah (swt), the Mighty and Majestic, and say what the mu'adhdhin says.\""
        ]
      }
    },
    "verse_translations": [
